File: A general view of the headquarters of Eskom. AFP/Gianluigi Guercia JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has announced that it will be implementing stage 2 power cuts from 5 pm to 10 pm on Saturday. Eskom says this is due to further loss in generating capacity. READ: Eskom implements Stage 1 power cuts from 5pm There are two 389 MW stations on maintenance while 17 810 MW station is down due to breakdowns. The power utility has warned if capacity is not increased, the blackouts will be repeated at the same time, throughout the week. #PowerAlert1
Due to a further loss of generating capacity, Stage 2 loadshedding will be implemented from 17:00 – 22:00 tonight. Loadshedding is likely be repeated at the same time throughout the week. pic.twitter.com/AD7mGKigS4 Power utility Eskom has announced that stage 2 power cuts will be implemented once again until 10 o'clock this evening. #DStv403 #Today pic.twitter.com/nNaCsYCDJR